OL,3,CAlcohol-free beer on draught 'helps
OL,4,Cpeople make healthy choices'
OL,6,FMaking alcohol-free beer more widely
OL,7,Favailable on draught nudges people
OL,8,Ftowards healthier choices, research
OL,9,Fsuggests.
OL,11,FA new study led by the University of
OL,12,FBristol found that making the drinks
OL,13,Fmore visible and easier to purchase in
OL,14,Fbars led to increases in sales of non-
OL,15,Falcoholic beer.
OL,17,FAlcohol can lead to weight gain,
OL,18,Faddiction and has been linked to seven
OL,19,Ftypes of cancer, including mouth,
OL,20,Fupper throat, larynx, oesophagus,
OL,21,Fbreast and bowel cancer.
