OL,3,CAlcohol-free beer on draught 'helps
OL,4,Cpeople make healthy choices'
OL,6,FFor the study, the pubs and bars
OL,7,Fcompleted two intervention periods and
OL,8,Ftwo "control" periods in a randomised
OL,9,Forder over eight weeks.
OL,11,FThe intervention involved replacing
OL,12,Fone draught alcoholic beer with an
OL,13,Falcohol-free beer. The control period
OL,14,Fof the study was business as usual.
OL,16,FThe study found that, when an alcohol-
OL,17,Ffree option was available, pubs and
OL,18,Fbars sold, on average, 29 fewer litres
OL,19,Fof alcoholic beer per week, equivalent
OL,20,Fto 51 fewer pints and a 5% reduction
OL,21,Fin sales.
