OL,6,FThe team, writing in the journal
OL,7,FAddiction, concluded: "Introducing a
OL,8,Fdraught alcohol-free beer in bars and
OL,9,Fpubs in England reduced the volume of
OL,10,Fdraught alcoholic beer sold by 4% to
OL,11,F5%, with no evidence of the
OL,12,Fintervention impacting net revenue."
OL,14,FDr Angela Attwood, associate professor
OL,15,Fin the Tobacco and Alcohol Research
OL,16,FGroup, said: "Although alcohol-free
OL,17,Foptions have been available for a
OL,18,Fwhile in pubs and bars, they have not
OL,19,Fhad the same visual prominence as
OL,20,Falcoholic drinks and are rarely served
OL,21,Fon draught.
