OL,4,Cpeople make healthy choices'
OL,6,F"Our study showed that providing front-
OL,7,Fof-bar draught non-alcoholic options
OL,8,Fcould lead to some customers switching
OL,9,Ffrom alcoholic drinks.
OL,11,F"This does not restrict consumer
OL,12,Fchoice; in fact, it increases the
OL,13,Foptions available to the customer, and
OL,14,Fat the same time could reduce
OL,15,Fpopulation levels of alcohol
OL,16,Fconsumption and improve public health."
